Custom Vocabulary: Challenges in understanding domain-specific jargon or acronyms.
Context Understanding: Maintaining context across long conversations for coherent analysis.
Multi-Speaker Identification: Differentiating between multiple speakers in overlapping conversations.
Sentiment Detection Accuracy: Difficulty in accurately detecting emotional tone from voice alone.
Model Generalization: Ensuring the model generalizes well across industries and conversation types.
Accents and Dialects: Handling diverse accents and dialects is complex for speech recognition.
Background Noise: Noisy environments reduce the clarity of transcriptions.



Data Silos: Difficulty in aggregating data from disparate supply chain systems.
Real-Time Data Integration: Challenges in continuously updating models with real-time supply chain data.
Scalability: Handling large-scale data across global supply chain networks.
Contextual Relevance: Ensuring relevant document retrieval from vast unstructured data sources.
Data Inconsistency: Variations in formats and quality of supply chain data complicate model training.
Latency in Query Processing: Slow response times in retrieving and generating insights from large datasets.
Fine-Tuning for Specific Domains: Customizing AI models to accurately reflect supply chain nuances.
Multi-Language Support: Handling multiple languages in global supply chain documentation.
Document Chunking: Breaking down large supply chain documents without losing critical context.
Dynamic Risk Modeling: Incorporating rapidly changing external risks into AI-driven forecasts.
Bias in Training Data: Inherent biases in historical supply chain data affect model outcomes.
Explainability of AI Decisions: Difficulty in interpreting and explaining complex AI-driven recommendations.
Supplier Privacy: Ensuring sensitive supplier information remains secure in the RAG pipeline.
Model Generalization: Ensuring the AI solution adapts to varying supply chain scenarios and disruptions.
Cost of Implementation: High computational resources required for processing large, real-time supply chain datasets.
